default2.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultUKLPG is the one voice of the LP Gas industry in the UK, representing an industry worth over £750 million to the economy and employing over 10,000 people.
default&#xa0;
default2.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultUKLPG represents all the major LPG distribution companies, retailers and equipment suppliers in the UK and a number of producers. Member companies cover over 95% of the total LPG sales in the UK.  
default&#xa0;
default2.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLP Gas is sold into bulk tanks at customers’ locations in
default off grid areas, or in cylinders for portable use throughout the UK. LP
default 
defaultG
defaultas
default is used in rural areas of the UK as a source of domestic and commercial heating and cooking, as well as agricultural grain drying and poultry rearing, and finally as a transport fu
defaultel.
default&#xa0;
default2.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPropane and Butane gases, collectively known as LPG (Liquefied Petroleum Gas) are sourced either from separating the products from natural gas streams, or from oil refinery processes. LP
default 
defaultG
defaultas 
defaultis a relatively small part of the barrel, some 2-3% of the o
defaultutput of refined products, but is used extensively for off grid domestic and commercial heating - as is portable bottled gas - in industrial processes and in the petro-chemical industry. 
default&#xa0;
default2.5.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultA total of 3.5 million tonnes of LP Gas is used in the UK, of which
default two thirds is used in the petro-chemical industry and the remaining third sold into the inland heating and industrial market. Two thirds of LP Gas produced in the UK comes from refinery production versus one third from gas separation.
default&#xa0;
default2.6.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLP
default 
defaultG
defaultas
default is cost effe
defaultctive due to its efficiency.  In its liquid form it is also so compact that one unit of gas holds the fuel of 270 units of gas.  LPG can be up to five times more efficient than traditional fuels.
