default&#xa0;default3.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultConsumption of energy for heat in the home is
default on a downward trend with promising new technologies offering further efficiency gains.
default The priority has to be to maintain this trend and the good news is that gas
default - including liquefied petroleum gas -
default technology still has an enormous amount to offer. For 
defaultexample, two thirds of properties still have older non-condensing boilers and therefore still have significant savings available at relatively low cost.
default There
default is also a raft of exciting new technologies coming on to the market which will further accelerate
default the decline in energy consumption and carbon emissions and can be used in off gas grid areas as well. 
