default&#xa0;
default3.7.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSignificant improvements in energy effic
defaultiency in the housing stock can be achieved through replacement of inefficient appliances by technologies such as the condensing boiler, which utilises the latent heat of water produced from the burning of fuel, in addition to the standard sensible heat, to
default increase its efficiency. Condensing technology, an established and cost-effective solution has a demonstrated potential to increase boilers efficiency by 15-20 percent as compared to their conventional equivalents. 
default&#xa0;
default3.8.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLPG and solar or wind energy are a natural partnership: Solar and wind are great examples of how LPG can offer reliability and security to renewables. LPG can be used as a primary or complementary source of energy, helping to overcome the intermittent natu
defaultre of these energy sources.
default These modern systems —often referred to as hybrids — combine the reliability of a conventional fuel with the numerous benefits of renewable energy to provide warm water for millions of consumers across Europe. Hybrid solutions c
defaultan also be desig
defaultned to meet space-heating needs.
